Craniops is an extinct genus of brachiopods in the family Craniopsidae with species known from the Ordovocian to the Devonian.
C. curvata, C. elegans, C. estona and C. obtusa are from the Kukruse Stage (Ordovician) of Kohtla-JÃ¤rve, in north-eastern Estonia.C. tenuis is a pooleville member of the Bromide Formation from the Middle and Upper Ordovician of Oklahoma.